00050 /* ============================================================================
00051  * Revision History
00052  * ================
00053  * 16-Sep-2008 Added Header File of MMC/SD CSL.
00054  * 16-Jun-2009 Added DMA mode support
00055  * 26-Jun-2009 Code modified as per review comments
00056  * 26-Jun-2009 Added SDHC card support
00057  * 25-Feb-2010 Added second callback support  KR022510
00058  * 10-Mar-2010 Pedro updates
00059  * 05-Apr-2010 - Incorporated Frank's comments
00060  * 06-Apr-2010 - Removed MMC_setDmaCallback() API as the functionality of
00061  *               DMA callback function is replaced by write done callback function
00062  * 06-Apr-2010 - Renamed write done callback function to data transfer callback
00063  *               since it is used by both MMC write and read APIs. Renamed
00064  *               all the related functions and data structures
00065  * 08-Apr-2010 - Formatted the code to have uniform style
00066  * 10-Apr-2010 - Added doxygen comments for few enums and structures
00067  * 12-Apr-2010 - Merged the code with CSL PG2.0 modifications
00068  *               Added Enum CSL_MmcsdEndianMode to choose the endian mode of MMCSD
00069  *               Added API prototype for MMC_setEndianMode()
00070  * 16-Apr-2010 - Added API SD_configurePullup() to configure SD card pull-up
00071  *               resistor
00072  * 19-Apr-2010 - Added APIs
00073  *             - MMC_setBlockLength()
00074  *             - MMC_setWriteBlkEraseCnt()
00075  *             - SD_setBusWidth()
00076  *             - MMC_getCardStatus()
00077  * 30-Apr-2010 - Incorporated internal review comments
00078  * 13-Aug-2010 CSL v2.10 release
00079  * 06-Jul-2011 CSL v2.50 release
00080  * 13-Sep-2012 CSL v3.00 release
00081  * 20-Dec-2012 CSL v3.01 release
00082  * 25-Feb-2012 - Removed the reduntant code of sending the commands to the Card,
00083  *               and replaced it with a call to the MMC_sendCmd() API.
00084  * ============================================================================
00085  */

03667  *****************************************************************************/
03713 static inline
03714 CSL_MMCSDEventType MMC_getEventId(
03715                           CSL_MmcsdHandle     hMmcsd)
03716 {
03717 
03718     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_DATDNE_MASK)
03719         return CSL_MMCSD_EDATDNE_INTERRUPT;
03720     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_BSYDNE_MASK)
03721         return CSL_MMCSD_EBSYDNE_INTERRUPT;
03722     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_RSPDNE_MASK)
03723         return CSL_MMCSD_ERSPDNE_INTERRUPT;
03724     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_TOUTRD_MASK)
03725         return CSL_MMCSD_ETOUTRD_INTERRUPT;
03726     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_TOUTRS_MASK)
03727         return CSL_MMCSD_ETOUTRS_INTERRUPT;
03728     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_CRCWR_MASK)
03729         return CSL_MMCSD_ECRCWR_INTERRUPT;
03730     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_CRCRD_MASK)
03731         return CSL_MMCSD_ECRCRD_INTERRUPT;
03732     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_CRCRS_MASK)
03733         return CSL_MMCSD_ECRCRS_INTERRUPT;
03734     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_DXRDY_MASK)
03735         return CSL_MMCSD_EDXRDY_INTERRUPT;
03736     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_DRRDY_MASK)
03737         return CSL_MMCSD_EDRRDY_INTERRUPT;
03738     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_DATED_MASK)
03739         return CSL_MMCSD_EDATED_INTERRUPT;
03740     if(hMmcsd->mmcRegs->MMCST0 & CSL_MMCSD_MMCST0_TRNDNE_MASK)
03741         return CSL_MMCSD_ETRNDNE_INTERRUPT;
03742 
03743     return CSL_MMCSD_INTERRUPT_NONE;
03744 }
